Class PrioritizedTypeConverter<From>

  • java.lang.Object
    • se.jguru.nazgul.core.reflection.api.conversion.registry.PrioritizedTypeConverter<From>

    Comparable<PrioritizedTypeConverter>

    public class PrioritizedTypeConverter<From>
extends Object
implements Comparable<PrioritizedTypeConverter>
    Holder class for a set of prioritized TypeConverter instances, all of which convert objects from a single source class/type.
    Author:
    Lennart Jörelid, jGuru Europe AB

      • add

        public void add(Object... converters)
        Validates and adds any converter instances from the supplied array, given that they convert sourceType instances to some other type.
        Parameters:
        converters - A list of potential converters, holding methods or constructors converting sourceType instances to some other type. Should any two converter methods (or constructors) have identical priority, fromType and toType the result is undefined in the sense that an arbitrary converter will be used.

      • getTypeConverters

        public <To> List<TypeConverter<From,To>> getTypeConverters(Class<To> targetType)
        Retrieves the prioritized list holding all known TypeConverters able to convert between the sourceType to the targetType of this PrioritizedTypeConverter instance.
        Type Parameters:
        To - The target Type desired.
        Parameters:
        targetType - The type to which all retrieved TypeConverters should be able to convert to.
        Returns:
        a prioritized list holding all known TypeConverters able to convert between the sourceType to the targetType.

      • convert

        public <To> To convert(From toConvert,
                       Class<To> toType)
        Performs a standard conversion from the supplied toConvert value to the given toType. The known converters will be attempted in correct priority order; the first TypeConverter instance which can handle the requested conversion will be executed to receive the results.
        Type Parameters:
        To - The type to convert to.
        Parameters:
        toConvert - The object which should be converted.
        toType - The type to convert to.
        Returns:
        null if toConvert could not be converted, and the resulting [converted] instance otherwise.
